Moonsville Collective @ Long Beach Folk Revival in Long Beach, CA
description:
The 4th Annual Long Beach Folk Revival Festival returns to Rainbow Lagoon Park on September 17th, 2016! 

 Without further ado, we are downright thrilled to present:
Nitty Gritty Dirt Band
 Celebrating 50 Years | Founded in Long Beach, CA in 1966

 WITH
The White Buffalo | Chuck Ragan (Official) | JD McPherson
Leo Bud Welch | Willy Tea Taylor | Big Sandy and his Fly-Rite Boys | The Lowest Pair | Moonsville Collective | Pearl Charles | Paige Anderson & The Fearless Kin | McDougall | Big Bad Rooster | Honey Whiskey Trio | The Hollow Trees | Echo Mountain | & introducing Smoggy Mountain String Band

http://www.folkrevivalfestival.com/tickets
 Ticket are on sale now and are $35 in advance 
 (pre-sale price to increase to $40 August 1st) 
 and $50 at the door.

 Kids 12 and under as well as Seniors 75 or older get in free.

 In addition to the great music, all the fan favorites from last year are back including the signature contests (pie eating, beard & mustache, banjo), amazing gourmet food trucks & craft beers, interactive kid’s area with the “Instrument Petting Zoo”, and the ever popular “Vintage Bazaar” shopping experience and Craft Pavilion.

 ABOUT OUR HEADLINER
 Founded in Long Beach, CA in 1966, The Nitty Gritty Dirt Band are celebrating their Golden (50th) Anniversary together and will headline this year’s Folk Revival Festival. Often cited as a catalyst for an entire movement in Country Rock and American Roots Music, garnering multi-platinum and gold records, strings of top ten hits such as "Fishin' In The Dark" and "Mr. Bojangles", multiple Grammy, IBMA, CMA Awards and nominations and their groundbreaking "Will The Circle Be Unbroken" album has recently been inducted into the U.S. Library of Congress as well as the Grammy Hall of Fame.

 "We're really excited to be coming back to Long Beach for the Folk Revival Festival this September! Most of us grew up there and our band got its start jamming at McCabe's in Long Beach in 1966, so it seems totally fitting that we celebrate our 50th Year in the city where it all began for NGDB!" says Jeff Hanna, founding Nitty Gritty Dirt Band member.

 It has been over 40 years since the Nitty Gritty Dirt Band has played a show in their hometown and they plan on Circlin’ Back to where it all started for one historic night in beautiful downtown Long Beach’s Rainbow Lagoon Park.


 _________________________________________________


 DIRECTIONS TO THE FESTIVAL

 The Folk Revival Festival is conveniently located in beautiful downtown Long Beach, CA right along the ocean front at Rainbow Lagoon Park. The official address is: E Shoreline Dr Long Beach, CA 90802

 We love to keep things green and sustainable at the festival and if you could help us out by using an alternative type of transportation to get here we would really appreciate it and so would Mother Earth!

 ON A BIKE

 We will have a bike valet at the festival FREE of charge for you to park your bike and not have to worry about it. It will be attended by good people at Bike Loca at all times. The festival location is nestled right along a Class I Bike Path that connects to the LA River Bike Path as well as the Beach Path just below the Bluffs that takes you all the way to Belmont Shore. 

 BY BUS

 Taking the bus is a great way to reduce that carbon footprint and once you are in downtown Long Beach you can catch the Passport bus for FREE and it takes you right to the festival location. 

 BY CAR

 If you have to come by car we ask that you carpool with a friend! Getting to the festival by car could not be any easier and all you have to do is take the 405 Fwy to the 710 Fwy South and the 710 turns into Shoreline Village Dr. 

 PARKING

 Parking around Rainbow Lagoon Park is plentiful and there are many options. The most convenient parking is adjacent to the park in the LB Convention Center Parking Lot which is $10 for all day parking as well as Shoreline Village & The Marina parking lots.


 FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS

 Do I need a ticket? And what is the cost?
 Yes. This is a ticketed event, but Kids 12 & under as well as Seniors 75 & over are FREE! Please refer to the TICKETS page for more info.

 What time does the show start?
 Doors open at 11am. The first musical act starts at 11:15 am. The festival is over at 11pm.

 What can I do after the festival is over?
 TBA

 Is there seating available?
 General Admission tickets for this event do not guarantee a seat. Seating is limited so please arrive early. We will be letting all patrons bring a low backed chair or blanket to sit on this year!

 Where can I eat?
 There will be gourmet food trucks & booths at our food court with a range of dining choices. No outside food or drink is permitted. More info on our vendors is on the Food & Craft Beer page.

 Is alcohol permitted?
 There will be several full service bars within the venue pouring your favorite local craft brews as well as hard liquor & wine. You may not bring alcohol into the venue and consumption of alcohol is not permitted in public spaces. See our Food & Craft Beer page for more details.

 Can I go in and out of the venue?
 Yes you can go in and out of the venue freely and we encourage you to check out the local shops, businesses, and art galleries near by.

 Is there an age limit to attend?
 The Folk Revival Festival is an all ages event, but alcohol will be served throughout the festival premises to those with a valid ID showing they are 21 years of age.

 Are pets allowed?
 Pets are NOT allowed at the festival.

 Is smoking permitted?
 Smoking is only permitted in the designated smoking areas or please step outside the event (at least 15 feet from the entrance) if you would like to smoke.

 What items are NOT allowed inside the venue?

 Bikes
 Glass bottles
 Food 
 Liquids in glass or plastic (other than 1 bottle of unopened water)
 Large Umbrellas
 Markers
 Weapons of any kind
 Professional video/audio equipment (contact media@folkrevivalfestival.com for more info)

 What happens if it rains?
 In the unlikely event that there is rain, we suggest you dress appropriately. LB Folk Revival Festival is a ‘rain or shine’ event.

 Will Recycling be available?
 Yes, recycling is available and we encourage you to use them and help us move closer to being a Zero waste event. Help us keep the park clean by leaving with all you came with! In addition we will also be composting food waste and biodegradable packaging. Please do your part to keep our festival green!

 Where is first aid located?
 If you require first aid assistance, please visit the Medical booth next to the Kids Area. If it is an emergency, please call 911.

 Where is the lost and found?
 Please visit the Ticket Booth/Tent for any lost items.

 For other questions: 
 info@folkrevivalfestival.com

title: Moonsville Collective @ TBA in Nashville, TN
description:
We are honored to perform at the 2016 Americana Music Awards Festival. 

All the info for tickets to the Festival is on their website. We will keep you posted with more details as we get closer. 


New to the Lineup Include: Amanda Shires, Billy Bragg & Joe Henry, 
 Bruce Hornsby & the Noisemakers, Dori Freeman, Howe Gelb, Jack Ingram, John Fullbright, John Prine, Kaia Kater, Motel Mirrors, 
 My Bubba, Sam Outlaw, Sean Watkins, Shawn Colvin & Steve Earle, 
 The Cordovas, The O'Connor Band featuring Mark O'Connor

Wristbands & Registrations On Sale Now!

                                                                                               
The Americana Music Association proudly unveiled its second round of AmericanaFest 2016 performers today. Additions to this year’s lineup include: Amanda Shires, Billy Bragg & Joe Henry, Bruce Hornsby & the Noisemakers, Dori Freeman, Howe Gelb, Jack Ingram, John Fullbright, John Prine, Kaia Kater, Motel Mirrors, My Bubba, Sam Outlaw, Sean Watkins, Shawn Colvin & Steve Earle, The Cordovas, and The O'Connor Band featuring Mark O'Connor.

Today’s additions bring the 17th Annual AmericanaFest artist list to 121 and more than 180 artists will be announced by the first week in September. 

Showcase wristbands are currently on sale ($60) and allow admission into all showcase venues, some sanctioned parties and special events, and can be purchased here. Festival and Conference registrations ($275 for members/$375 for non-members) offer priority admission into all showcase venues, sanctioned parties and events, daytime educational panels. Conference registrants may purchase a ticket to the Americana Honors & Awards show at the historic Ryman Auditorium, and can be purchased here.
